15 October 2019

FUNKIT IT - James Napier (jhn27) & Simon Lorimer (sal180)

About:
    This game is a take on bop it party mode for the UCFK4. It plays
    somewhat similarly with players having limited decreasing time to
    successfuly follow instructions on what button to press.

HOW TO PLAY:

Starting A Game:
    To start a game push the joy button down on one controller as per instructions
    led screen.
    
Playing A Game:
    Once one player has pressed the joy button down the game will start.
    The player who pressed the button down will start first. Push the joy in
    the direction shown on screen if an arrow is displayed or if a circle is 
    displayed push the joy down. This should be done before the timer runs out.
    Turn by turn the timer will speed up giving each player less time.
    The timer is shown as dots that count down across the top of the LED screen.
    Once one player fails they lose. The other player wins and the game is over.
    There will be coresponding feedback on each controller's LED screen.
    
Starting Another Game:
    When in winning or losing state push the joy down to reset to the start game screen.
    From here you can start another game as instructed earlier.
